//Must Do category They are a protected natural reservation in Romania, located at a distance of 6 km west from Turda, along the valley Hasdate. The length of the of the Turda Keys is of 2.900 m. The walls height is up to 300 m. The surface occupied by the Keys is of 125 ha and were formed by the erosion of the jurassic limestone rock by the river Hasdate. It is a fortification built during the Habsburg period on the top of the hill with the same name in Cluj-Napoca, in the Gruia district The Salt Mine is now a veritable history museum of salt mining. The excellent state of preservation of mining and machinery used to transport salt, together with the cautious work carried out for prepararing the mine to become a tourist attraction, have made history and legend meet harmoniously here. It is a Gothic-style Roman Catholic church in Cluj-Napoca. It is the second largest church (after the Black Church of Brașov) in the geographical region of Transylvania, Romania. This classified historic monument, conceived by János Fadrusz and opened in 1902, represents Matthias Corvinus. It is a historic monument in Romania
//Parks category The park is bounded by the Cluj Arena to the west, the Hungarian State Theater to the East, the Somesul Mic River to the north, and the Iuliu Hossu (formerly Pavlov) to the south. It is listed on the historical monuments list in Cluj County In addition to its role as a tourist destination, the garden also serves as a teaching and research center as part of the Babeș-Bolyai University. In 2010, the Romanian Ministry of Culture and National Patrimony categorized it as a historical monument. It is a small park featuring a lake and it is situated in the vecinity of Iulius Mall. A very old park in one of the older neighbourhoods of the city. It has recently been revamped and features a brand new Skatepark. The most modern sports and leisure complex in Cluj made with European funds.
//Shopping category Opened in 2007 and oriented towards multiculturalism, IULIUS MALL CLUJ provides an original mix of its multiple uses and the fondness of Transylvanian locals for art in all its forms. VIVO! was launched in October 2014. The brand represents the shopping centers that address small and medium-sized towns in the urban agglomerations in the east and central Europe. Features 30 shops of recognized international. A great place to dine. 14 new events organized every month.
//History category is the most famous Romanian Orthodox church of Cluj-Napoca, Romania. Built in a Romanian Brâncovenesc style, a synthesis of Renaissance and Byzantine architecture, it lies on the Avram Iancu Square is a place of worship in Cluj-Napoca, Romania. It was built between 1260 and 1290, on the site of an older Catholic church destroyed during the Tatar invasions in 1241. With a history of more than 80 years, the Ethnographic Museum of Transylvania is one of the first and greatest of its kind in Romania. It has two exhibition sections, one of which is to be found in downtown Reduta Palace (21, Memorandumului Street), while the other exhibition section is the open-air Romulus Vuia Park situated on the city\'s north-west side, in Hoia Forest. The Pharmacy History Collection can be found in the oldest pharmacy building of Cluj-Napoca, named “La Sfântul Gheorghe”, also known as the Hintz pharmacy, dating back to 1573. With a collection of over 12,000 paintings, sculptures, graphic arts and decorative pieces, it is considered one of the most important museums in Romania. Since 2008 the Observatory organizes activities for the general public also. Visitors are welcome every Friday night, after dark, for a program scheduled for 2 hours. It consists of an introduction (projecting a simulated configuration of the sky map of the moment accompanied by an explanation of the celestial objects that will be observed), and a practical, observational part, using the existing instruments.
//Nightlife category Londoner takes us to London, where people have a strange but sophisticated accent, where we seem to look through the fogs and the specific English hats. Located in the historic center of the city, in the basement of a building, Flying Circus Pub is a club for young indie, rock, punk, or electronic music lovers. Shto College Bar is the place where you can find good music, fine people, products for all tastes and a very friendly atmosphere! The Bruno Wine Bar and Bistro, a little spotless, an introduction to the particularities of wines on 4 continents, in the careful balance of "l'apéritif et le digestif" plus a selection of fine cheeses and snacks in perfectly balanced combinations because at just as with a successful "marriage", wine and food can not be separated. Casa Tauffer is the only exclusive jazz and blues café in the city, opened in 2010, located in the historic monument building, In the 18th century the first (unofficially, of course) Iosefine (Radical) masonry was functioning, and then the first literary (German) salon in Cluj. the place where fashion, luxury and fun meet and merge, metamorphosed in a complete, complete, round, unforgettable experience.
